<section id="loading">
  <header>
    <h2>Loading / Success states</h2>
  </header>

	<p><strong>Stateful buttons</strong> keep users oriented during async work. Swap in the loading variant the moment a submission begins, then transition to success when the operation completes so the button itself narrates progress without forcing someone to hunt for <em>a detached status message</em>.</p>

	<div class="section-example">
  	<button class="loading">Loading</button> 
  	<button class="primary loading">Loading</button> 
  	<button class="secondary loading">Loading</button> 
  	<button class="positive loading">Loading</button> 
  	<button class="negative loading">Loading</button>

  	<br>
  	  	
  	<button class="loading success">Success</button> 
  	<button class="primary loading success">Success</button> 
  	<button class="secondary loading success">Success</button> 
  	<button class="positive loading success">Success</button> 
  	<button class="negative loading success">Success</button>
  </div>

	<p class="note"><strong>Preserve button width</strong> when swapping labels or spinners to prevent layout shift, and expose the same status via <code>aria-live</code> regions so assistive tech can <em>announce completion</em>.</p>

  <div class="code-example">
    <pre><code class="html">&lt;button class="loading"&gt;...&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button class="loading success"&gt;...&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>
  </div>
</section>


